# chat 3
Lead Conversion Model - Chat Summary
ðŸ” Problem Identified
Data Leakage Discovery: Found that sc1_to_conversion_days feature was using future information (conversion dates) that wouldn't be available at prediction time. This was creating artificially high performance.
ðŸ› ï¸ Model Refinement Process
Step 1: Removed Leaky Feature

Eliminated sc1_to_conversion_days
Result: ROC-AUC dropped from 0.81 to 0.809 (minimal impact - proved model was mostly legitimate)

Step 2: Strategic Pivot to Early-Stage Model

Key Insight: Predicting conversion after sales call attendance is less valuable than predicting it earlier
Decision: Remove ALL sales call (SC) and follow-up (FU) related features
Focus on booking call data only for earlier intervention

Step 3: Early-Stage Model Results

ROC-AUC: 0.814 (actually improved!)
Accuracy: 69% (acceptable drop)
Business Impact at 0.4 threshold:

Call 2,562 leads instead of 7,674 (33% of total)
Catch 82.7% of converters (81 out of 98)
3.0x efficiency gain



ðŸŽ¯ Final Model Characteristics
Features Used: Only booking call data (BC_1 through BC_18 outcomes, dates)

No sales call attendance info
No future conversion dates
Clean, production-ready features

Key Predictive Features:

last_bc_outcome_encoded
engagement_score
outcome_trend
total_bc_attempts
Booking call behavioral patterns

ðŸ’¼ Business Value
Deployment Strategy: Early-stage scoring right after booking calls complete

Timing: Score leads immediately after BC completion
Implementation: Ready for Airflow pipeline integration
ROI: 3x more efficient lead prioritization

Recommendation: Use 0.4 threshold for optimal balance of recall (82.7%) and efficiency (3.0x gain).
ðŸš€ Status
Production-ready model with legitimate predictive power and clear business impact. No data leakage, actionable timing, ready for automated deployment.

# observation: 
Business Recommendation:
Score leads after their 2nd or 3rd booking call attempt - this gives you:

Enough data for reliable predictions
Still early enough for intervention
Good balance of timing and accuracy

Airflow Implementation:
Trigger scoring when total_bc_attempts >= 2 rather than on a fixed schedule. This ensures you always have sufficient data for meaningful predictions.